Korean Pension Fund Plans to Invest $4 Billion Abroad, WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-02-17T07:37:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/korean-pension-fund-plans-to-invest-4-billion-abroad-wsj-says.html
Korean National Pension Fund
Service, the world’s fourth-biggest pension fund, plans to
invest $4 billion in overseas projects this year, some on
infrastructure and some in the U.S., the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Jun Kwang-
woo.  Jun said he wants to broad NPS’s invstment in so-called
alternative assets, in other words anything that isn’t based on
equity and fixed-income; the fund’s assets hit $268 billion at
the end of 2010 and are expected to almost quadruple over the
next 10 years, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  